    "body": "Unfortunately, the browser is handling copy-pasting, and in particular on Mac OS X, it is trying to do \"Smart\" things (like smart quotes, space after/before punctuation...), and despite bug report and feature requests to have the ability disable that, a lot have been denied, or ignored. \n\nThe next version will have search and replace (wit reg-ex support) so that should help. \n\nAlso in general issues about the notebook should be opened on the [notebook](https://github.com/jupyter/notebook) repository. But I understand that what is which component on on which repo to open what can be confusing. \n"
